19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
22 Human Services from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
23 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
24 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Two Hundred Seventy-two Thousand
Req. No. 3914 Page 1

1 Doll ars ($272,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to
2 carry out the provisions of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1847 of the 2nd
3 Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
4 SECTION 2. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
5 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
6 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Seven Million Seven
7 Hundred Twenty-nine Thousand One Hundred Ninety-seven Dollars
8 ($7,729,197.00) shall be used to replace funding no longer available
9 due to the reduction of federal matching dollars.
10 SECTION 3. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
11 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
12 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the Department shall maintain the
13 funding levels for senior nutrition programs from the fiscal year
14 ending June 30, 2026. The Oklahoma Legislature requires joint
15 approval from the President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate
16 and the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives before any
17 senior nutrition sites may be closed due to declining attendance or
18 increased operational costs during the fiscal year ending June 30,
19 2027.
20 SECTION 4. In addition to the funding required in Section 3 of
21 this act, from the funds appropriated to the Department of Human
22 Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session of the
23 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Two Million Five Hundred
24
Req. No. 3914 Page 2

1 Thou sand Dollars ($2,500,000.00) shall be used to maintain the
2 permanent second meal per day for the ADvantage Waiver Program.
3 SECTION 5. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
4 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
5 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Five Million Dollars
6 ($5,000,000.00) shall be used to carry out the provisions of
7 Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1806 of the 2nd Session of the 60th
8 Oklahoma Legislature.
9 SECTION 6. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
10 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
11 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Two Hundred Fifty
12 Thousand Dollars ($250,000.00) shall be used to carry out the
13 provisions of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1377 of the 2nd Session of
14 the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
15 SECTION 7. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
16 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
17 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Four Million Five
18 Hundred Sixty Thousand Dollars ($4,560,000.00) shall be used to
19 carry out the provisions of Enrolled House Bill No. 2778 of the 1st
20 Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
21 SECTION 8. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
22 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
23 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of Twenty-five Million
24 Five Hundred Seventy-five Thousand Dollars ($25,575,000.00) shall be
Req. No. 3914 Page 3

1 used to provide additional state funding for the administration of
2 the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program.
3 SECTION 9. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
4 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
5 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the Department is authorized to
6 transfer the sum of Three Million Dollars ($3,000,000.00) to the 2-
