13 ($38,993,761.00) shall be used to provide additional state funding
14 for the ADvantage waivers.
15 SECTION 11. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
16 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
17 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the Department shall maintain the
18 funding levels for provider rates and service authorizations for the
19 Community, Homeward Bound, In-Home Supports for Adults, In-Home
20 Supports for Children, and ADvantage waivers from the fiscal year
21 ending June 30, 2026.
22 SECTION 12. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
23 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
24 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature for the support of the
Req. No. 3914 Page 4

1 Deve lopmental Disability Services Division, in addition to services
2 provided in the fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, the agency may
3 also budget for and expend funds for family and self-advocate
4 onboarding meetings and services, professional development for case
5 management and providers, expansion of crisis services, and
6 enhancements to intake processes for the purpose of ensuring a
7 stronger, more responsive service delivery system for Oklahomans
8 with developmental disabilities.
9 SECTION 13. From the funds authorized to be transferred to the
10 Developmental Disability Services Revolving Fund in Enrolled Senate
11 Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature,
12 no funds may be expended for administrative services, targeted case
13 management, Medicaid match for any ICF/IID services or other non-
14 Medicaid match services not described in Section 11 of this act.
15 SECTION 14. From the funds appropriated to the Department of
16 Human Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177 of the 2nd Session
17 of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the Department of Human Services
18 shall transfer Five Million Six Hundred Thousand Dollars
19 ($5,600,000.00) to the credit of the Child Abuse Multidisciplinary
20 Account established in Section 1-9-103 of Title 10A of the Oklahoma
21 Statutes, which shall be distributed according to Section 1-9-104 of
22 Title 10A of the Oklahoma Statutes.
23 SECTION 15. There is hereby appropriated to the Department of
24 Human Services all federal monies received by the state during the
Req. No. 3914 Page 5

1 fisc al year ending June 30, 2027, from the Temporary Assistance for
2 Needy Families Block Grant and the Child Care and Development Block
3 Grant to meet the provisions of federal law relating to such grants.
4 SECTION 16. The Director of Human Services may request through
5 the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services the
6 early transfer by the Oklahoma Tax Commission of tax collections to
7 the General Revenue Fund for the purpose of early allocation to the
8 Department of Human Services disbursing funds to alleviate cash flow
9 problems.
10 SECTION 17. A. The Director of the Office of Management and
11 Enterprise Services shall transfer monies appropriated from the
12 General Revenue Fund to the Department of Human Services disbursing
13 funds in the amounts and ratios requested by the agency except that
14 the cumulative amount transferred shall not exceed the cumulative
15 amount of equal monthly allotments of the appropriations from the
16 General Revenue Fund.
17 B. Monies appropriated or collected for the fiscal year ending
18 June 30, 2027, may be transferred to these disbursing funds for the
19 fiscal year ending June 30, 2026, to satisfy encumbrances and
20 obligations of the fiscal year, provided that monies equal in amount
21 are transferred from appropriations or collections for the fiscal
22 year ending June 30, 2026, to the disbursing funds for the fiscal
23 year ending June 30, 2027, to satisfy encumbrances and obligations
24
Req. No. 3914 Page 6

1 of t he fiscal year. All transfer requests shall be in writing to
2 the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services.
3 C. The Department of Human Services shall maintain records of
4 such inter-year transfers.
5 SECTION 18. The Director of Human Services may request the
6 Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services to
7 transfer monies between the Department of Human Services Support
8 Service Providers Grant Program Fund and the Human Services
9 Disbursing Fund or the Human Services Medical and Assistance Fund,
10 as needed for the expenditure of funds.
11 SECTION 19. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
12 SECTION 20. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
13 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
14 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
15 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
